data.title: LingoAce gains WASC accreditation, setting new standards in supplemental education, joining elite institutions.
data.description: A prominent Edtech company, LingoAce, has recently achieved full accreditation from a highly respected accrediting body. This recognition places LingoAce among an exclusive group that includes private schools, public schools, and institutions. The accreditation was awarded in Singapore and San Mateo, California on February 27, 2026. LingoAce, known for its innovative educational solutions, is now part of a select few recognized for meeting the rigorous standards set by this accrediting body.

data.title: National Hardware Show Concept to Commerce in Las Vegas, March 31-April 2, 2026. Renovated format connecting retail industry.
data.description: From March 31 to April 2, 2026, Las Vegas will host the leading event for product discovery and sourcing in the retail industry. Known as NHS Concept to Commerce 2026, this event aims to revolutionize the way retailers engage with new products. It will feature a new format and promises to be a must-attend for industry professionals.

data.title: Afghan artist Sonita launches "Donate Your Voice" campaign with UNICEF to give voice to silenced Afghan women.
data.description: Singer and activist Sonita Alizadeh has introduced the "Donate Your Voice" campaign to combat the silence faced by women in Afghanistan. This initiative, in collaboration with UNICEF, encourages individuals worldwide to contribute their voices using a TikTok filter. The campaign was launched in Paris on February 27, 2026.

data.title: Metacon received EUR 2.6 million payment from Motor Oil Hellas for a 50 MW electrolysis plant project milestone.
data.description: In a recent development, Metacon, based in Stockholm, announced on Feb. 27, 2026, that they have successfully received a payment of EUR 2.6 million from Motor Oil Hellas. This amount corresponds to approximately SEK 27.7 million based on the current exchange rate. This payment was made in relation to achieving a significant milestone in the project to supply a 50 MW electrolysis plant. The project's progress underscores the partnership between Metacon and Motor Oil Hellas as they work towards the successful delivery of this substantial electrolysing facility.

data.title: Duolingo's Q4 sales beat estimates at $282.868 million but forecasts for FY2026 at $1.197-1.221 billion were lower than expected.
data.description: Duolingo Inc (DUOL) announced strong fourth-quarter sales of $282.868 million, surpassing market expectations of $275.925 million. However, their sales forecast for FY2026 falls below estimates, with expected revenues between $1.197 billion to $1.221 billion, compared to the projected $1.264 billion. The company highlighted the impact of AI advancements on learning methods and expressed a strategic shift towards prioritizing user growth and enhancing teaching quality. Duolingo aims to enhance the free learner experience to drive organic growth and expand into new sectors like chess, math, and music, which may temporarily impact financial growth. This shift positions Duolingo for future success. For more information, refer to the complete story on Benzinga.com.
